why are the kentucky police destroying pappy van winkle bourbon type to search like us on facebook follow us on twitter esquire follow us on pinterest esquire breaking news this is the most hellish marathon in the world how often should you replace your athletic shoes heres how to wake up betterlooking  outfits to wear to the beach this summer what age is the best age why are kentucky police destroying pappy van winkle bourbona sad day for bourbon fans most popular getty by aaron goldfarb jan   bourbon brands arent usually trending topics on twitter and facebook nor do they often make the nightly news but such was the case back in  when  cases of the legendary pappy van winkle were stolen the kentuckybased company was trending again last year when authorities took down a softballplayin guntotin steroidtraffickin organized crime ring and retrieved some of that stolen hooch and here we find ourselves this week talking about pappy van winkle once moreadvertisement  continue reading belowfirst came the news that the franklin county sheriffs office would be auctioning off  of the recovered bottles everyone celebrated now comes the sad news that the van winkle family has asked a judge to have those bottles destroyed and everyone cried whyyet i cant help thinking all this talk over  measly bottlesof course this is no ordinary bourbon pappy van winkle has become the most famous whiskey in america a unicorn unseen on store shelves for years untasted by the vast majority of humans and sold for astronomical sums on the secondary market those  bottles have a retail value of around  and a secondary value of perhaps  depending on age that may sound like a lot but its not i wouldnt be surprised if buffalo trace—the distiller of the van winkle line—washes that much whiskey down the drain every week most popularso whats the big dealthe whiskey lovers boo and the conspiracy theorists say the van winkles are loving the attention…again explained acclaimed bourbon writer fred minnickthe van winkles are if anything masters at getting and then keeping their name and their eponymous bourbons name in the headlines im not claiming julian van winkle iii—grandson of pappy and president of the old rip van winkle distillery note not an actual distillery—orchestrated this theft but the outspoken man and his famed family have yet again taken a minor story and managed to keep it in the news cycle all week longas always these pappy tales have absolutely nothing to do with the actual taste of the products my reviews pappy  year is as worldclass as bourbon comes while the  and  years suffer from an overwoodiness instead the story once again is about how rare this product is—though really not that rare with about  bottles produced per year—and how every bottle lost is yet another bottle you will likely never tasteof course we cant ignore the fact that no one knows what the hell happened to those  bottles while they were out of buffalo traces controlwhere is the precedent for a sheriffs department auctioning alcohol or a controlled substance minnick added believing the bourbon should be destroyed how do we know the steroidslinging child pornhaving criminals didnt tamper with the whiskeyits a valid point still destroy it or not i would bet the van winkles dont really care what happens to these  bottles it wont affect their bottom line nor the perceived quality of their product but ultimately it will have more people writing about their bourbon and arguing about it and wondering just how good it truly is and ultimately coveting it even more than they already dopappy van winkle may have been a great bourbon maker but his grandson continues to be the pt barnum of bourbon mythmakingmore from esquire more fromdrinks beverage share how to make a gimlet beverage share how to make a mint julep beverage share beat the  pm slump with this essential coffee cocktailcreated for starbucks doubleshot drinks share dare halle berry to chug whiskey and she will chug whiskey drinks share  notbad nonalcoholic beers beverage share how to make a classic mimosa drinks share ted danson will return to curb your enthusiasm and he promises its wonderfully insane drinks share  chefs reveal their secret hangover cures drinks share jim beams newest release wont be a bourbon beverage share how to make a cosmopolitan food  drink drinks bourbon kentucky pappy van winkle what will the future of pappy van winkle taste like the idiots guide to not drinking pappy van winkle inside the pappy van winkle forgery scheme thats infiltrating bourbons black market this is about destroying the presidency of barack obama fast fashion is absolutely destroying the planet so this is why the nypd is destroying all those illegal dirt bikes more from drinks pappy van winkles family reserve  wikipedia pappy van winkles family reserve from wikipedia the free encyclopedia jump to navigation search pappy van winkle bourbon whiskey bottle of pappy van winkle type bourbon whiskey manufacturer sazerac company country of origin kentucky united states alcohol by volume – proof us – related products buffalo trace pappy van winkles family reserve is the flagship brand of bourbon whiskey owned by the old rip van winkle distillery company which does not actually own or operate a distillery but rather has it produced under a contract with another company it is distilled and bottled by the sazerac company at its buffalo trace distillery in frankfort kentucky pappy van winkles family reserve is often regarded as one of the finest bourbons in the world and is rare to find on the market due to its very low production and high demand contents  history  popularity among bourbon enthusiasts  style  awards  limited edition decanter   theft  forgeries and counterfeit bourbon  see also  references  further reading  external links historyedit in  when he was  years old julian pappy van winkle sr began working as a salesman for the liquor wholesaler wl weller  sons fifteen years later he and another weller salesman bought the firm in  they acquired the a ph stitzel distillery in louisville kentucky which had started as a sour mash whiskey distillery in  the stitzel distillery supplied much of the whiskey sold by the weller wholesale firm the consolidation coincided with prohibition during which time the stitzelweller firm was licensed by the government to produce whiskey for medicinal purposes one of their labels that was introduced on the market just before prohibition was old rip van winkle after prohibition the brand was not reintroduced until after  when the stitzelweller distillery and its current brand names including wl weller old fitzgerald rebel yell and cabin still were sold to other companies the only brand name the van winkle family kept the rights to was the preprohibition brand old rip van winkle the stitzelweller distillery was opened on the day of the kentucky derby in  just outside louisville in shively kentucky at the time of his death in  at the age of  pappy van winkle was the oldest active distiller in the nation a photo of him graces the bottles label sometime after the stitzelweller distillery was sold in  julian van winkle jr resurrected the preprohibition old rip van winkle brand and initially used old whiskey stocks from the distillery for its bottlings julian jr died in  and julian van winkle iii pappys grandson took over the old rip van winkle distillery company after the initial sale in  the stitzelweller distillery was eventually closed completely in  in  buffalo trace distillery commercially marketed the first modern posts brand of singlebarrel bourbon blantons since  the van winkle brands have been distilled and bottled by the sazerac company at the buffalo trace distillery as a joint venture with the old rip van winkle distillery company in  julian preston van winkle iii said the  bottlings of the year brand expression may be the last of its kind since at that point there was very little left of the aging stock from the stitzelweller distillery although he said the brand would not be discontinued the makers say that they do not want to boost production as there is considerable long term risk and they do not want to be left holding copious quantities of unsaleable bourbon should tastes fashions or circumstances change production is being increased somewhat with a projected increase of the annual production from the current – thousand bottles to  thousand by  but the production will remain well below massmarket levels popularity among bourbon enthusiastsedit the product has a cultlike following famous chefs such as anthony bourdain and david chang have favored the product food republic reported that chef john currence said theres pappy van winkle then theres everything else bourbon aficionados have shown up in droves to get a small chance in a lottery to purchase some it has been called the bourbon everyone wants but no one can get a writer for the wall street journal said you could call it bourbon or you could call it a  bottle of liquified barrelaged unobtanium jen doll wrote in the wire its an ageold dilemma supply and demand leading to an ageold marketing dream a product that cant be kept on the shelves  money in the pockets  bourbon in the bourbon snifters according to fox news and maxim pvw is said to be one of the most expensive bourbons styleedit like all modern bourbons van winkle bourbons are made primarily from corn and aged in charred new oak barrels a distinguishing feature of van winkle bourbons is their use of wheat as the secondary ingredient instead of the usual rye and their additional inclusion of barley malt pappy van winkle is aged for   or  years which is considerably longer than the aging period for most bourbons the  year is bottled at  us proof  alcohol by volume and has been described as intensely fruity the  year is bottled at  proof the  year is bottled at  proof awardsedit pappy van winkles family reserve has won various awards pappy van winkle  year old family reserve won a double gold medal at the  san francisco world spirits competition pappy van winkles family reserve  year old bourbon was named spirit of the year for  by wine  spirits magazine in its annual buying guide issue the  year old special reserve was recognized with the trophy for worldwide whisky and a bestinclass gold medallion in the  international wine and spirit competition it received a score of  superlative from the beverage testing institute in the same year a rating from the beverage testing institute created the pappy frenzy the  rating for the year pappy van winkle was the highest rating ever thus pappy was rescued from schmaltzy marketing hell and exploded into the cult it is today limited edition decanteredit the van winkles released a special limited edition decanter set of specially selected old rip van winkle  year old  proof van winkle bourbon barreled in the spring of   theftedit in midoctober  the company reported the theft of  threebottle cases of pappy van winkle  year and nine threebottle cases of yearold van winkle family reserve rye police theorized that it took the thief about two months to complete the heist and noted that whoever did it avoided being recorded by security cameras on monday december  sheriff melton announced a  reward to anyone who could give information that leads to a conviction in the case  of this reward money was offered by bluegrass crimestoppers and the other  by an anonymous donor a break in the case came in march  when a buffalo trace employee was arrested by franklin county authorities when five barrels of stolen wild turkey bourbon were found on his property on april   nine kentucky residents three of whom were employees at both wild turkey and buffalo trace were indicted for thefts at the buffalo trace and wild turkey distilleries dating back to  over  worth of the stolen whiskey was recovered including more than two dozen bottles of pappy van winkle and  barrels of wild turkey the van winkle family has stated that the stolen whiskey should be destroyed as a precaution against tampering or contamination pending the approval of the judge the heists included pappy van winkle more than  cases  to  cases of eagle rare bourbon and stolen barrels of other whiskey that are still missing the warrants recovered one barrel of yearold eagle rare worth more than  all nine defendants are charged with being members of a criminal syndicate engaging in organized crime forgeries and counterfeit bourbonedit empty bottles have turned up on ebay at extravagant prices it turns out that the bottles are being recycled refilled with counterfeit bourbon and sold as true pappy see alsoedit old fitzgerald old rip van winkle referencesedit  a b c d e f g h old rip van winkle  a b c d doll jen november   the bourbon everyone wants but no one can get the atlantic retrieved december     a b c d e f gabriel trip october   the case of the missing bourbon the new york times frankfort kentucky retrieved october     a b simpson connor october   where did the missing  cases of pappy van winkle whiskey go the atlantic retrieved october     a b moss josh witzke chris photographer july  the best bourbon youll never taste inside the pappy van winkle phenomenon louisville magazine louisville kentucky –  retrieved july     a b c hunt kristin  things you didnt know about pappy van winkle the washington post thrillist retrieved august     a b lipman linda lipman john american whiskey commonwealth distillery  where old rip van winkle sleeps american whiskey retrieved october     a b hall gregory a october   bourbon heist pappy van winkle stolen in apparent inside job the courierjournal retrieved october     a b g worth of rare expensive bourbon swiped from ky distillery fox news october   retrieved october     van winkle family heritage archived july   at the wayback machine  ellen jaye american whiskey – ghosts of the past old fitzgerald – the stitzelweller distillery – september     pappy van winkles family reserv