permanent linkpage informationwikidata itemcite this page printexport create a bookdownload as pdfprintable version in other projects wikimedia commons languages deutsch edit links this page was last edited on  july  at  text is available under the creative commons attributionsharealike license additional terms may apply by using this site you agree to the terms of use and privacy policy wikipedia® is a registered trademark of the wikimedia foundation inc a nonprofit organization privacy policy about wikipedia disclaimers contact wikipedia developers cookie statement mobile view pappy van winkles family reserve  wikipedia pappy van winkles family reserve from wikipedia the free encyclopedia jump to navigation search pappy van winkle bourbon whiskey bottle of pappy van winkle type bourbon whiskey manufacturer sazerac company country of origin kentucky united states alcohol by volume – proof us – related products buffalo trace pappy van winkles family reserve is the flagship brand of bourbon whiskey owned by the old rip van winkle distillery company which does not actually own or operate a distillery but rather has it produced under a contract with another company it is distilled and bottled by the sazerac company at its buffalo trace distillery in frankfort kentucky pappy van winkles family reserve is often regarded as one of the finest bourbons in the world and is rare to find on the market due to its very low production and high demand contents  history  popularity among bourbon enthusiasts  style  awards  limited edition decanter   theft  forgeries and counterfeit bourbon  see also  references  further reading  external links historyedit in  when he was  years old julian pappy van winkle sr began working as a salesman for the liquor wholesaler wl weller  sons fifteen years later he and another weller salesman bought the firm in  they acquired the a ph stitzel distillery in louisville kentucky which had started as a sour mash whiskey distillery in  the stitzel distillery supplied much of the whiskey sold by the weller wholesale firm the consolidation coincided with prohibition during which time the stitzelweller firm was licensed by the government to produce whiskey for medicinal purposes one of their labels that was introduced on the market just before prohibition was old rip van winkle after prohibition the brand was not reintroduced until after  when the stitzelweller distillery and its current brand names including wl weller old fitzgerald rebel yell and cabin still were sold to other companies the only brand name the van winkle family kept the rights to was the preprohibition brand old rip van winkle the stitzelweller distillery was opened on the day of the kentucky derby in  just outside louisville in shively kentucky at the time of his death in  at the age of  pappy van winkle was the oldest active distiller in the nation a photo of him graces the bottles label sometime after the stitzelweller distillery was sold in  julian van winkle jr resurrected the preprohibition old rip van winkle brand and initially used old whiskey stocks from the distillery for its bottlings julian jr died in  and julian van winkle iii pappys grandson took over the old rip van winkle distillery company after the initial sale in  the stitzelweller distillery was eventually closed completely in  in  buffalo trace distillery commercially marketed the first modern posts brand of singlebarrel bourbon blantons since  the van winkle brands have been distilled and bottled by the sazerac company at the buffalo trace distillery as a joint venture with the old rip van winkle distillery company in  julian preston van winkle iii said the  bottlings of the year brand expression may be the last of its kind since at that point there was very little left of the aging stock from the stitzelweller distillery although he said the brand would not be discontinued the makers say that they do not want to boost production as there is considerable long term risk and they do not want to be left holding copious quantities of unsaleable bourbon should tastes fashions or circumstances change production is being increased somewhat with a projected increase of the annual production from the current – thousand bottles to  thousand by  but the production will remain well below massmarket levels popularity among bourbon enthusiastsedit the product has a cultlike following famous chefs such as anthony bourdain and david chang have favored the product food republic reported that chef john currence said theres pappy van winkle then theres everything else bourbon aficionados have shown up in droves to get a small chance in a lottery to purchase some it has been called the bourbon everyone wants but no one can get a writer for the wall street journal said you could call it bourbon or you could call it a  bottle of liquified barrelaged unobtanium jen doll wrote in the wire its an ageold dilemma supply and demand leading to an ageold marketing dream a product that cant be kept on the shelves  money in the pockets  bourbon in the bourbon snifters according to fox news and maxim pvw is said to be one of the most expensive bourbons styleedit like all modern bourbons van winkle bourbons are made primarily from corn and aged in charred new oak barrels a distinguishing feature of van winkle bourbons is their use of wheat as the secondary ingredient instead of the usual rye and their additional inclusion of barley malt pappy van winkle is aged for   or  years which is considerably longer than the aging period for most bourbons the  year is bottled at  us proof  alcohol by volume and has been described as intensely fruity the  year is bottled at  proof the  year is bottled at  proof awardsedit pappy van winkles family reserve has won various awards pappy van winkle  year old family reserve won a double gold medal at the  san francisco world spirits competition pappy van winkles family reserve  year old bourbon was named spirit of the year for  by wine  spirits magazine in its annual buying guide issue the  year old special reserve was recognized with the trophy for worldwide whisky and a bestinclass gold medallion in the  international wine and spirit competition it received a score of  superlative from the beverage testing institute in the same year a rating from the beverage testing institute created the pappy frenzy the  rating for the year pappy van winkle was the highest rating ever thus pappy was rescued from schmaltzy marketing hell and exploded into the cult it is today limited edition decanteredit the van winkles released a special limited edition decanter set of specially selected old rip van winkle  year old  proof van winkle bourbon barreled in the spring of   theftedit in midoctober  the company reported the theft of  threebottle cases of pappy van winkle  year and nine threebottle cases of yearold van winkle family reserve rye police theorized that it took the thief about two months to complete the heist and noted that whoever did it avoided being recorded by security cameras on monday december  sheriff melton announced a  reward to anyone who could give information that leads to a conviction in the case  of this reward money was offered by bluegrass crimestoppers and the other  by an anonymous donor a break in the case came in march  when a buffalo trace employee was arrested by franklin county authorities when five barrels of stolen wild turkey bourbon were found on his property on april   nine kentucky residents three of whom were employees at both wild turkey and buffalo trace were indicted for thefts at the buffalo trace and wild turkey distilleries dating back to  over  worth of the stolen whiskey was recovered including more than two dozen bottles of pappy van winkle and  barrels of wild turkey the van winkle family has stated that the stolen whiskey should be destroyed as a precaution against tampering or contamination pending the approval of the judge the heists included pappy van winkle more than  cases  to  cases of eagle rare bourbon and stolen barrels of other whiskey that are still missing the warrants recovered one barrel of yearold eagle rare worth more than  all nine defendants are charged with being members of a criminal syndicate engaging in organized crime forgeries and counterfeit bourbonedit empty bottles have turned up on ebay at extravagant prices it turns out that the bottles are being recycled refilled with counterfeit bourbon and sold as true pappy see alsoedit old fitzgerald old rip van winkle referencesedit  a b c d e f g h old rip van winkle  a b c d doll jen november   the bourbon everyone wants but no one can get the atlantic retrieved december     a b c d e f gabriel trip october   the case of the missing bourbon the new york times frankfort kentucky retrieved october     a b simpson connor october   where did the missing  cases of pappy van winkle whiskey go the atlantic retrieved october     a b moss josh witzke chris photographer july  the best bourbon youll never taste inside the pappy van winkle phenomenon louisville magazine louisville kentucky –  retrieved july     a b c hunt kristin  things you didnt know about pappy van winkle the washington post thrillist retrieved august     a b lipman linda lipman john american whiskey commonwealth distillery  where old rip van winkle sleeps american whiskey retrieved october     a b hall gregory a october   bourbon heist pappy van winkle stolen in apparent inside job the courierjournal retrieved october     a b g worth of rare expensive bourbon swiped from ky distillery fox news october   retrieved october     van winkle family heritage archived july   at the wayback machine  ellen jaye american whiskey – ghosts of the past old fitzgerald – the stitzelweller distillery – september     pappy van winkles family reserve could be last of its kind whiskeycaskcom august   retrieved october     a b c gara tom july   pappy van winkle the bourbon so popular even billionaires cant find it the